Senior Managing Director of Apollo Global Management (NYSE:APO), Rowan Marc J, sells 565,900 shares worth $15,142,975
According to Apollo Global Management's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated May 04 07:09 PM, company Senior Managing Director, Rowan Marc J disclosed selling 565,900 shares at a cost of $26.76. At the time of this transaction (May 02), this trade was worth $15,142,975 in total. As of May 02, Rowan Marc J now owns 495,397 shares in total worth about $12,959,585.52. 
For the last few recent trades made by Apollo Global Management (NYSE:APO) Senior Managing Director, Rowan Marc J, we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: May 03: Sold 346,043 shares at the rate of $26.50 per share. Total worth of this trade was $9,168,478. Total number of shares owned as of May 03 were 149,354
SEC Form 4 filing: May 04: Sold 149,354 shares at the rate of $26.08 per share. Total worth of this trade was $3,895,735. Total number of shares owned as of May 04 were 0
SEC Form 4 filing: May 01: Sold 188,703 shares at the rate of $26.82 per share. Total worth of this trade was $5,060,165. Total number of shares owned as of May 01 were 1,061,297




